quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to position the caption of the table at the bottom:
[!raw!]
caption {
   caption-{0}: {1};
}

Fill in the blanks to hide the empty cells of the table.
[!raw!]
table {0}
  empty-cells: {1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The table-layout Property[/h1]

The [b]table-layout[/b] specifies how the width of table columns is calculated. The possible values are:
[b]auto [/b]- when column or cell width are not explicitly set, the column width will be in proportion to the amount of content in the cells that make up the column
[b]fixed [/b]- when column or cell width are not explicitly set, the column width will not be affected by the amount of content in the cells that make up the column.

The table layout is set to [b]auto [/b]by default. 
The example below shows the difference between auto and fixed. 

[b]The HTML:[/b][code format="html" ]<p>Table-layout is set to <strong>auto</strong></p>
<table class="auto">
  <tr>
    <td width=â€œ10%">500.000.000.000.000</td>
    <td width="90%">20.000</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>Table-layout is set to <strong>fixed</strong></p>
<table class="fixed">
  <tr>
    <td width="10%">500.000.000.000.000</td>
    <td width="90%">20.000</td>
  </tr>
</table>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="559"]table {
   border-collapse: separate;
   width: 100%;
   border: 1px solid gray;
} 
td {
   border: 1px solid gray;
}
table.[b]auto [/b]{
   table-layout: auto;
}
table.[b]fixed[/b] {
   table-layout: fixed;
}[/code]
